## `echo` and `eval`

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="50%"}

`echo: false`

evaluate code without showing it <br>

Text here...

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 3.142857
```
:::
:::


more text here
:::

::: {.column width="50%" .fragment}

`eval: false`

show code without evaluating it <br>

Text here...

::: {.cell}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
#| eval: false
a <- 22
a / 7
```
````
:::

<br>
more text here
:::

::::

## `warning: false`

Warning is **not** printed to the console when rendering


::: {.cell}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
#| warning: false
ggplot(msleep, aes(sleep_rem, sleep_total)) + 
  geom_point()
```
````

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](w6_quarto_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-24-1.png){width=864}
:::
:::


## `warning: true`

Warning **is** printed to the console when rendering


::: {.cell}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
#| warning: true
ggplot(msleep, aes(sleep_rem, sleep_total)) + 
  geom_point()
```
````

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}
```
Warning: Removed 22 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).
```
:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](w6_quarto_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-25-1.png){width=864}
:::
:::


## `error: true`

This will show errors in the rendered document


::: {.cell}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
#| error: true

ggplot(msleep, aes(sleep_rem, sleep_total)) + 
  geom_point())
```
````

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-error}
```
Error: <text>:2:15: unexpected ')'
1: ggplot(msleep, aes(sleep_rem, sleep_total)) + 
2:   geom_point())
                 ^
```
:::
:::


## `error: false`

The document won't render if it encounters an error

